WEBVTT

1
00:01:29.590 --> 00:01:31.133
Oh, bollocks.

2
00:01:35.763 --> 00:01:36.806
We've got a problem.

3
00:01:36.931 --> 00:01:39.475
A cyber attack?
Yes, Prime Minister.

4
00:01:39.558 --> 00:01:42.478
Took me
two bottles of wine

5
00:01:42.561 --> 00:01:45.398
and half a packet of sleeping
pills to finally nod off.

6
00:01:45.523 --> 00:01:50.027
And you wake me because some fat-fingered
hacker's pinched your PIN number?

7
00:01:50.319 --> 00:01:51.862
Well, it's a little more serious
than that, Prime Minister.

8
00:01:51.946 --> 00:01:53.864
Hmm?
The identities of every one

9
00:01:53.948 --> 00:01:55.950
of our serving agents
have been exposed.

10
00:01:56.951 --> 00:01:57.994
What?

11
00:01:58.119 --> 00:02:00.121
Who's doing this?
We're not sure, ma'am.

12
00:02:00.246 --> 00:02:03.040
So one week before I host
my first G12 Summit,

13
00:02:03.124 --> 00:02:05.334
Britain's entire security
apparatus has been taken down

14
00:02:05.459 --> 00:02:06.836
and you know
absolutely nothing?

15
00:02:06.919 --> 00:02:09.672
That does pretty much sums up
the situation, ma'am, yes.

16
00:02:09.797 --> 00:02:11.674
Well, you better get someone
on it and find me some answers!

17
00:02:11.757 --> 00:02:13.968
Yes, but that's the problem.
We don't have any agents left.

18
00:02:14.051 --> 00:02:15.094
They've all been outed.

19
00:02:15.344 --> 00:02:17.596
So bring back an old one!

20
00:02:31.402 --> 00:02:35.489
All units, this is Juliet Echo.
Stand by for target coordinates.

21
00:02:37.992 --> 00:02:41.996
Target acquired.
Repeat, target acquired.

22
00:03:00.014 --> 00:03:02.808
Now then, what have we here?

23
00:03:05.102 --> 00:03:06.228
Sorry, sir.

24
00:03:06.395 --> 00:03:07.980
Never mind, Baggaley.

25
00:03:08.064 --> 00:03:11.108
Your concealment and camouflage
work is definitely improving.

26
00:03:11.233 --> 00:03:12.318
Thank you, sir.

27
00:03:12.526 --> 00:03:13.527
Come on.

28
00:03:13.611 --> 00:03:15.529
You, too, Ibadulla.

29
00:03:15.654 --> 00:03:18.824
Excellent. That is
a first-class man-trap.

30
00:03:19.533 --> 00:03:21.369
Yes!
Six house points.

31
00:03:23.120 --> 00:03:25.331
Right, let's get back
to school before matron

32
00:03:25.414 --> 00:03:26.665
notices you're missing.

33
00:03:26.874 --> 00:03:29.418
And don't worry, there aren't
any more booby traps.

34
00:03:32.254 --> 00:03:34.590
Apart from this one,
of course.

35
00:03:49.730 --> 00:03:50.815
Mr. English?

36
00:03:51.107 --> 00:03:52.608
We haven't seen him, sir.

37
00:03:53.067 --> 00:03:54.193
Huh.

38
00:03:55.403 --> 00:03:58.239
And that's camouflage.

39
00:04:00.991 --> 00:04:02.159
Hmm.

40
00:04:06.497 --> 00:04:07.498
And go.

41
00:04:08.582 --> 00:04:09.667
And go.

42
00:04:10.501 --> 00:04:11.877
And go.

43
00:04:12.086 --> 00:04:15.005
The welfare of your children
is our paramount concern.

44
00:04:15.381 --> 00:04:17.383
They're never exposed
to any unnecessary risk,

45
00:04:17.466 --> 00:04:18.884
I assure you.

46
00:04:29.770 --> 00:04:33.899
I think that's an "F" for your bomb
disposal coursework, Hattersley.

47
00:04:34.358 --> 00:04:37.027
"You're looking particularly
beautiful tonight."

48
00:04:37.153 --> 00:04:40.573
You're looking
particularly beautiful tonight.

49
00:04:40.865 --> 00:04:41.866
"Ching!"

50
00:04:42.199 --> 00:04:43.451
Ching!

51
00:04:45.536 --> 00:04:48.080
Have a good half-term, sir!
Thank you.

52
00:05:41.050 --> 00:05:43.302
Are you seriously telling me
this is all we've got?

53
00:05:43.427 --> 00:05:44.762
Most of them are either dead,

54
00:05:44.845 --> 00:05:47.681
having hip operations or
recovering from prostate surgery.

55
00:05:49.767 --> 00:05:50.768
Okay.

56
00:05:51.393 --> 00:05:55.147
Before your briefing, we'll need
you to re-sign the Official Secrets Act.

57
00:05:55.272 --> 00:05:56.440
Thank you.

58
00:05:56.815 --> 00:05:57.858
Thank you.

59
00:05:57.942 --> 00:05:58.943
Thank you.

60
00:05:59.443 --> 00:06:00.945
Thank you very much.

61
00:06:01.362 --> 00:06:03.614
Any of you
gentlemen remember this?

62
00:06:04.073 --> 00:06:07.618
Ooh, the Mont Blanc Blaster.
Haven't seen one of those for years.

63
00:06:07.868 --> 00:06:12.540
Take the cap off and, if memory
serves, you've 20 seconds to replace it

64
00:06:12.665 --> 00:06:15.501
or it detonates with the force
of a stun grenade.

65
00:06:35.980 --> 00:06:37.314
Thank you.

66
00:06:39.984 --> 00:06:42.361
Teas on the left, gentlemen.

67
00:06:42.486 --> 00:06:44.446
And coffees on the right.

68
00:06:44.738 --> 00:06:45.948
Excellent.

69
00:06:46.073 --> 00:06:49.034
Oh, damn it,
I forgot my pills.

70
00:06:49.201 --> 00:06:51.328
Here, have some of mine.

71
00:06:52.913 --> 00:06:54.999
Scotch whisky, single malt?

72
00:06:55.124 --> 00:06:56.959
Thank you very much.

73
00:06:57.167 --> 00:06:59.169
Coffee.
Oh.

74
00:06:59.253 --> 00:07:01.505
Here, let me
help you with that.

75
00:07:06.802 --> 00:07:07.886
Tea?

76
00:07:13.350 --> 00:07:16.145
Ooh, this one just needs
a little top-up of hot water.

77
00:07:16.770 --> 00:07:18.230
I'll be right back.

78
00:07:20.107 --> 00:07:22.359
Man's a divot
of the first order.

79
00:07:22.443 --> 00:07:24.778
Someone should put him
out of his misery.

80
00:07:24.903 --> 00:07:27.948
Along with whoever
furnished this room.

81
00:07:34.038 --> 00:07:35.205
Oh!

82
00:07:37.499 --> 00:07:39.501
Ah, good morning.
Sorry to keep you.

83
00:07:41.462 --> 00:07:43.213
Are the others here?

84
00:07:43.505 --> 00:07:44.757
Um...

85
00:07:45.841 --> 00:07:47.009
Oh.

86
00:07:51.305 --> 00:07:54.725
They, um... They nodded off.

87
00:07:55.267 --> 00:07:56.268
Right...

88
00:07:57.519 --> 00:07:58.812
And who are you exactly?

89
00:07:59.313 --> 00:08:00.397
English.

90
00:08:01.357 --> 00:08:03.067
- Johnny English.
- Well...

91
00:08:04.526 --> 00:08:06.028
"English..."

92
00:08:07.363 --> 00:08:08.822
You'll leave immediately.

93
00:08:08.906 --> 00:08:10.991
My people will give you
the full briefing en route.

94
00:08:11.075 --> 00:08:12.409
Oh, is there
anything you need?

95
00:08:12.493 --> 00:08:16.205
Yes, nerve gas nasal spray,
a type-four exoskeleton...

96
00:08:16.330 --> 00:08:18.248
You should probably
start a list.

97
00:08:18.374 --> 00:08:21.794
And a garroting watch, with a
rubber strap, not the steel bracelet

98
00:08:21.919 --> 00:08:25.255
because the links get caught
in the little hairs on my wrist.

99
00:08:25.589 --> 00:08:27.675
Oh, and I'll also
need a Bough.

100
00:08:28.217 --> 00:08:29.718
What's a Bough?

101
00:08:31.095 --> 00:08:32.096
Sir!

102
00:08:34.181 --> 00:08:36.016
Wonderful to see you!

103
00:08:37.226 --> 00:08:39.937
Yes, all right, Bough. We're going
on a mission, not a honeymoon.

104
00:08:40.187 --> 00:08:41.772
Yes, of course, sir.

105
00:08:42.398 --> 00:08:45.442
Ah. I think it's the pin of your
buckle, sir. It's caught on my jumper.

106
00:08:45.526 --> 00:08:46.735
Yes, I can see
what's wrong, Bough.

107
00:08:46.902 --> 00:08:50.072
If you go to your left
and I'll go to my right.

108
00:08:51.448 --> 00:08:54.702
I'm sorry, no, if you go to
your right and I'll go to my left.

109
00:08:56.745 --> 00:09:00.290
No. If I go clockwise
and you go anti-clockwise...

110
00:09:01.250 --> 00:09:02.751
Er, no, I think that's
making it worse, sir.

111
00:09:02.835 --> 00:09:05.254
Hmm. I'm surprised
that didn't work.

112
00:09:10.509 --> 00:09:13.679
Good morning, sir. I have your
agent activation pack here.

113
00:09:14.221 --> 00:09:15.889
Department-issue smartphone.

114
00:09:15.973 --> 00:09:20.269
580-megapixel camera,
4.7-inch retina HD display.

115
00:09:20.352 --> 00:09:25.357
Hmm-hmm. Ingenious. And what
does it shoot? Poison darts?

116
00:09:25.983 --> 00:09:29.695
It doesn't shoot anything.
It's a phone.

117
00:09:30.279 --> 00:09:32.197
There's a Twitter handle,
Instagram feed

118
00:09:32.281 --> 00:09:34.283
and secure login for the
department Uber account.

119
00:09:34.366 --> 00:09:35.367
What's he on about, Bough?

120
00:09:35.451 --> 00:09:37.578
I need a weapon.
Not a box of gobbledygook.

121
00:09:37.786 --> 00:09:40.122
I think, uh,
what Agent English

122
00:09:40.205 --> 00:09:42.499
is getting at, sir, is all
this is highly trackable.

123
00:09:42.791 --> 00:09:46.170
But since we're dealing with a
very sophisticated, digital target,

124
00:09:46.253 --> 00:09:50.841
we might be less visible if we took
a more analog, low-tech approach.

125
00:09:52.509 --> 00:09:53.594
Exactly.

126
00:09:55.012 --> 00:09:56.346
I see.

127
00:09:56.889 --> 00:09:58.682
Is there anything else
I can get you?

128
00:09:59.099 --> 00:10:00.434
A gun.

129
00:10:01.977 --> 00:10:06.148
We don't really
do guns anymore.

130
00:10:06.523 --> 00:10:08.108
Just get him a gun.

131
00:10:08.525 --> 00:10:09.818
Right, a gun.

132
00:10:16.450 --> 00:10:19.536
Right. Haven't actually done
one of these before.

133
00:10:20.704 --> 00:10:22.831
"It is my obligation
under section 14

134
00:10:22.915 --> 00:10:24.708
"of the Health and Safety
Directive to inform you

135
00:10:24.792 --> 00:10:27.461
"that the equipment with which
you are about to be issued

136
00:10:27.544 --> 00:10:29.463
"can cause injury
and bodily harm.

137
00:10:33.383 --> 00:10:36.011
"Furthermore, any agents
with nut allergies

138
00:10:36.094 --> 00:10:37.221
"should be aware
that traces of cashew oil..."

139
00:10:37.304 --> 00:10:38.639
Thank you.

140
00:10:41.266 --> 00:10:42.684
Right, transport.

141
00:10:46.480 --> 00:10:48.524
So, take any hybrid you want.

142
00:11:04.414 --> 00:11:05.666
I'll take this one.

143
00:11:05.916 --> 00:11:08.961
Oh, don't be ridiculous,
English. This car is a relic.

144
00:11:09.044 --> 00:11:11.839
Drinks petrol, leaks oil
and has no passive,

145
00:11:11.922 --> 00:11:13.590
let alone
active safety features.

146
00:11:13.799 --> 00:11:15.217
Do you know what else
it doesn't have, sir?

147
00:11:15.300 --> 00:11:18.053
Satellite navigation
or a single computer chip.

148
00:11:18.136 --> 00:11:21.390
Making it completely invisible
to a digital enemy.

149
00:11:23.392 --> 00:11:25.477
The equipment
Agent English requested, sir.

150
00:11:25.561 --> 00:11:26.770
Thank you.

151
00:11:27.896 --> 00:11:29.690
Phone, Bough?
Yeah.

152
00:11:32.860 --> 00:11:36.071
That hi-tech villain of yours
will never see us coming.

153
00:11:53.589 --> 00:11:55.424
Let's see
what they've given us.

154
00:11:56.133 --> 00:12:00.846
Exoskeleton, exploding cotton
buds, the old shoebox inflatable.

155
00:12:00.929 --> 00:12:02.139
Hmm.

156
00:12:03.098 --> 00:12:07.477
Ooh, what are these? Instant
Release Super High Energy Pills.

157
00:12:07.686 --> 00:12:11.815
Like sticking your fingers in an
electric socket. Highly recommended.

158
00:12:12.733 --> 00:12:15.861
Right, so, the red ones must be
the Total Knockout Sleeping Pills.

159
00:12:15.986 --> 00:12:17.070
Correct.

160
00:12:17.154 --> 00:12:19.448
Hmm. Probably worth
labeling these.

161
00:12:19.531 --> 00:12:20.574
Oh.

162
00:12:20.657 --> 00:12:23.076
Look, sir. Sweeties.

163
00:12:24.077 --> 00:12:25.162
Ooh.

164
00:12:25.704 --> 00:12:27.456
Hang on a minute.

165
00:12:27.581 --> 00:12:29.416
I always did love
a jelly baby.

166
00:12:29.499 --> 00:12:32.586
I wouldn't if I was you, Bough.
"Jelly" is short for gelignite.

167
00:12:32.669 --> 00:12:34.379
One bite and it'll take
the top of your head off

168
00:12:34.463 --> 00:12:36.131
along with
the roof of the car.

169
00:12:36.715 --> 00:12:38.467
So, what does this do?

170
00:12:39.718 --> 00:12:41.595
It's a mixtape, Bough.

171
00:12:46.016 --> 00:12:48.685
- So, destination?
- South of France, sir.

172
00:12:48.769 --> 00:12:50.771
That cyber attack
seems to have been launched

173
00:12:50.854 --> 00:12:53.315
from the Wi-Fi signal
of a hotel in Antibes.

174
00:13:38.068 --> 00:13:41.363
Sir? Sir, I've just had
a fax through from HQ.

175
00:13:41.780 --> 00:13:44.908
Background checks on all the
guests that accessed the Wi-Fi network.

176
00:13:44.992 --> 00:13:47.119
You see? Who needs email?

177
00:13:52.874 --> 00:13:54.126
Um...

178
00:13:54.209 --> 00:13:56.545
One name has raised
a red flag, sir.

179
00:13:57.337 --> 00:14:00.257
Sebastian Lynch, ex-Army
and Military Intelligence.

180
00:14:00.507 --> 00:14:03.343
Now selling his services
to the highest bidder.

181
00:14:03.635 --> 00:14:06.304
Where do we find him?
Directly ahead, sir.

182
00:14:07.973 --> 00:14:11.184
He's got an 8:00 reservation
at the Cote de Roc restaurant.

183
00:14:21.778 --> 00:14:24.990
The problem's going to be getting
close enough for a full surveillance, sir.

184
00:14:25.240 --> 00:14:27.159
Not necessarily.

185
00:14:43.967 --> 00:14:47.054
Oh, darling, I've
just gotta get this. Two seconds.

186
00:14:47.637 --> 00:14:51.975
Simple plan, two parts. You provide
the distraction, I'll get the phone.

187
00:14:52.059 --> 00:14:54.394
Yes, sir.
And from now on,

188
00:14:54.770 --> 00:14:59.733
perhaps
we should sound like French waiters.

189
00:15:01.401 --> 00:15:03.278
French waiters?

190
00:15:04.154 --> 00:15:05.405
Yees.

191
00:15:06.948 --> 00:15:08.116
Go on.

192
00:15:13.872 --> 00:15:15.916
Are you finished now,
Sebastian?

193
00:15:17.209 --> 00:15:18.710
Bread roll?

194
00:15:18.960 --> 00:15:20.045
Yes, thank you.

195
00:15:20.420 --> 00:15:22.380
Excellent choice,
<i>madame.</i>

196
00:15:23.840 --> 00:15:25.258
Good evening.

197
00:15:25.842 --> 00:15:27.427
How are you?

198
00:15:29.221 --> 00:15:30.722
Bread roll, sir?

199
00:15:30.847 --> 00:15:32.265
Yes. Thank you.

200
00:15:37.270 --> 00:15:38.563
One second.

201
00:15:38.855 --> 00:15:40.774
Excuse me,
would you mind?

202
00:15:41.608 --> 00:15:43.819
Oh, yes. Evening.

203
00:15:44.402 --> 00:15:45.487
Evening.

204
00:15:59.835 --> 00:16:01.169
Thank you.

205
00:16:15.433 --> 00:16:16.601
Where's my phone?

206
00:16:18.270 --> 00:16:19.646
That is your phone.

207
00:16:21.731 --> 00:16:23.567
Ooh.

208
00:16:28.238 --> 00:16:29.239
Thank you.

209
00:16:30.532 --> 00:16:31.575
<i>Monsieur.</i>

210
00:16:32.742 --> 00:16:36.037
The, uh, shell on my wife's
lobster, could you remove it, please?

211
00:16:38.248 --> 00:16:39.416
Yees.

212
00:16:40.208 --> 00:16:42.127
Uh...
Um...

213
00:16:42.377 --> 00:16:43.545
Hmm.

214
00:16:47.549 --> 00:16:49.843
Let me crack it for you.

215
00:17:03.690 --> 00:17:05.025
Oh!

216
00:17:05.817 --> 00:17:06.985
Ow!

217
00:17:38.433 --> 00:17:39.601
Hello?

218
00:17:42.687 --> 00:17:44.981
Steve, I'll have
to call you back. Call you back.

219
00:17:47.234 --> 00:17:48.485
Give me a sec. Hang on.

220
00:17:49.903 --> 00:17:51.446
What is going on?

221
00:17:54.950 --> 00:17:56.993
Sebastian,
don't get involved.

222
00:18:00.330 --> 00:18:01.665
Ah.

223
00:18:05.877 --> 00:18:08.338
- What is he doing?
- I don't know. He's a fool.

224
00:18:09.422 --> 00:18:11.007
There we are.

225
00:18:13.260 --> 00:18:14.469
<i>Voilà.</i>

226
00:18:21.851 --> 00:18:24.104
Hmm. Bon appétit.

227
00:18:27.232 --> 00:18:30.360
I will talk to the manager.
I will talk to the manager.

228
00:18:39.536 --> 00:18:41.621
Textbook, Bough.

229
00:18:46.084 --> 00:18:47.919
Just
holiday snaps, sir.

230
00:18:49.129 --> 00:18:51.047
Wait a minute, this photo.

231
00:18:51.298 --> 00:18:55.135
It was taken the same day our
villain accessed the Wi-Fi, and look.

232
00:18:55.802 --> 00:18:57.762
Scarcely 50 feet from shore.

233
00:18:59.556 --> 00:19:00.932
Whoever was on that yacht

234
00:19:01.016 --> 00:19:03.768
could easily have used
the hotel's Wi-Fi,

235
00:19:03.852 --> 00:19:07.022
sent that signal
and then just sailed away.

236
00:19:07.564 --> 00:19:12.235
I think it's time
we paid the <i>Dot Calm</i> a visit.

237
00:19:24.956 --> 00:19:25.957
<i>Algorithms.</i>

238
00:19:26.041 --> 00:19:28.251
<i>We are surrounded by them.</i>

239
00:19:28.335 --> 00:19:30.503
<i>Algorithms run our lives,</i>

240
00:19:30.587 --> 00:19:35.050
<i>choose our TV shows, stream
our music. Even find us a date.</i>

241
00:19:37.093 --> 00:19:38.845
I know this chap, don't I?

242
00:19:38.970 --> 00:19:42.223
Yes, he's that Silicon Valley
billionaire who dated a Kardashian.

243
00:19:42.307 --> 00:19:45.018
Two Kardashians and a
Black-Eyed Pea. Keep watching.

244
00:19:45.185 --> 00:19:48.438
<i>But supposing there was an
algorithm for an entire country.</i>

245
00:19:48.521 --> 00:19:52.108
<i>A single algorithm that could be
applied to every one of its problems.</i>

246
00:19:52.359 --> 00:19:56.529
<i>A single algorithm that could take
a second-rate nation and make it</i>

247
00:19:57.072 --> 00:19:58.948
<i>world class.</i>

248
00:20:00.283 --> 00:20:02.702
<i>Every nation
is awash with data.</i>

249
00:20:03.411 --> 00:20:08.041
So now, more than ever, we need
to put that data to work for the people.

250
00:20:08.541 --> 00:20:11.419
These few lines of code
will deliver the kind of change

251
00:20:11.544 --> 00:20:14.297
they have been dreaming of
their entire lives.

252
00:20:14.422 --> 00:20:17.467
<i>I am Xander. I love data.</i>

253
00:20:20.678 --> 00:20:22.430
He's so clever.

254
