505
00:44:21.993 --> 00:44:23.411
Never mind!

506
00:44:29.209 --> 00:44:31.461
<i>With what
appears to be another cyber attack,</i>

507
00:44:31.545 --> 00:44:32.838
<i>pressure is mounting
on the Prime Minister.</i>

508
00:44:32.963 --> 00:44:34.923
Every train in England?
Yes, sir.

509
00:44:35.006 --> 00:44:38.093
They're all trying to terminate
at Bristol Temple Meads.

510
00:44:41.304 --> 00:44:42.347
Morning, sir!

511
00:44:42.430 --> 00:44:44.516
You see this, English?
Yes!

512
00:44:45.433 --> 00:44:46.434
Please.

513
00:44:47.227 --> 00:44:48.562
Ooh!

514
00:44:49.145 --> 00:44:51.606
Tell me you've got something I
can take to the Prime Minister.

515
00:44:51.690 --> 00:44:54.693
Would the name of the man
responsible do, sir?

516
00:44:55.026 --> 00:44:56.611
Excellent, English, yes.

517
00:44:57.237 --> 00:44:59.531
It's Jason...

518
00:45:09.708 --> 00:45:12.168
Volta, sir. Jason Volta.

519
00:45:12.586 --> 00:45:13.587
What?

520
00:45:13.753 --> 00:45:16.339
You're accusing the PM's
knight in shining armor?

521
00:45:16.423 --> 00:45:18.258
I'd need hard evidence.

522
00:45:25.390 --> 00:45:26.725
Which...

523
00:45:27.475 --> 00:45:29.978
...is why Agent English
is proposing

524
00:45:30.061 --> 00:45:32.606
a penetration of Volta's
country estate in Surrey.

525
00:45:32.814 --> 00:45:37.068
Yes, yes, yes, yes...

526
00:45:37.152 --> 00:45:39.487
Well, do what you have
to do, English.

527
00:45:39.863 --> 00:45:41.865
But for God's sake,
be discreet about it.

528
00:45:42.073 --> 00:45:44.117
Oh! Oh.

529
00:45:44.200 --> 00:45:45.243
Good.

530
00:45:45.327 --> 00:45:46.411
Oh. Oh.

531
00:45:52.667 --> 00:45:54.377
"Virtual reality"?

532
00:45:54.502 --> 00:45:55.503
That's right, sir.

533
00:45:55.587 --> 00:45:57.923
P's built a computer model of
the inside of Volta's mansion.

534
00:45:58.006 --> 00:46:02.969
When you put on this headset, it will look
and feel as if you are inside the house.

535
00:46:03.053 --> 00:46:06.514
You'll be able to open and close
doors, walk up and down staircases,

536
00:46:06.598 --> 00:46:09.392
completely familiarize
yourself with its layout.

537
00:46:09.476 --> 00:46:12.729
This floor moves in any
direction. So you can walk...

538
00:46:13.980 --> 00:46:17.400
You can walk as far as
you want in the virtual world

539
00:46:18.151 --> 00:46:20.612
without ever actually
leaving this room.

540
00:46:20.987 --> 00:46:22.030
One thing though, sir.

541
00:46:23.239 --> 00:46:24.950
The experience can be
very disorientating.

542
00:46:25.033 --> 00:46:26.242
It's completely immersive

543
00:46:26.326 --> 00:46:29.371
and some people lose all track
of their actual surroundings.

544
00:46:29.454 --> 00:46:32.666
I think we can pretty much
guarantee that's not gonna happen.

545
00:46:32.999 --> 00:46:35.335
I'll just need you to sign the
health and safety releases.

546
00:46:35.669 --> 00:46:38.380
Would you excuse
me while I find an iPad.

547
00:46:39.381 --> 00:46:42.676
Oh, go with him, Bough. If we don't
chivvy him along we'll be here all day.

548
00:46:48.723 --> 00:46:49.975
Hmm.

549
00:47:10.161 --> 00:47:11.329
Ah.

550
00:47:33.393 --> 00:47:34.394
Watch out!

551
00:48:02.672 --> 00:48:04.466
<i>Door closing.</i>

552
00:48:05.091 --> 00:48:06.426
<i>Going down.</i>

553
00:49:07.153 --> 00:49:08.321
Hey!

554
00:49:23.795 --> 00:49:25.380
I'm sorry, sir, but you're
going to have to leave.

555
00:49:25.713 --> 00:49:26.756
Ow.

556
00:49:27.048 --> 00:49:28.091
Ow.

557
00:49:51.739 --> 00:49:54.868
So, we'll shortly
be arriving at Admiralty House.

558
00:49:54.993 --> 00:49:58.913
And, er, that actually used to be
Oliver Cromwell's own house. Um...

559
00:50:00.707 --> 00:50:02.041
Uh...

560
00:50:02.167 --> 00:50:05.670
And then we'll be going
to Horse Guards Parade.

561
00:50:08.423 --> 00:50:10.216
Perhaps you'd like
to sit down, sir?

562
00:50:12.969 --> 00:50:14.846
Hey, whoa!

563
00:50:19.475 --> 00:50:20.894
I've got them!

564
00:50:25.565 --> 00:50:29.527
However, the agent we have on this mission
is confident he's making major progress.

565
00:50:29.611 --> 00:50:32.405
And, uh, yes, we have a potential
suspect, he's been identified.

566
00:50:32.906 --> 00:50:36.910
And further covert
investigations are now ongoing.

567
00:50:38.203 --> 00:50:39.412
Yes, quite.

568
00:50:39.662 --> 00:50:42.582
So I expect to have more
to announce on this front

569
00:50:44.334 --> 00:50:45.501
shortly.

570
00:50:59.390 --> 00:51:00.558
Oh.

571
00:51:01.434 --> 00:51:02.435
Sir?

572
00:51:02.518 --> 00:51:03.645
Mmm?

573
00:51:03.728 --> 00:51:06.564
Is everything all right, sir?
Yes, I've done it, Bough.

574
00:51:06.814 --> 00:51:09.567
Child's play. Don't know what
all the fuss was about.

575
00:51:23.164 --> 00:51:25.166
<i>Pleasure to see you again,
Prime Minister.</i>

576
00:51:26.793 --> 00:51:29.712
It's a hologram.
Apparently you just speak to it normally.

577
00:51:31.381 --> 00:51:33.549
The pleasure's all mine.

578
00:51:33.633 --> 00:51:37.512
Hate to rush you, but was there
something in particular you needed?

579
00:51:37.595 --> 00:51:40.265
Actually, I was just calling
really to see

580
00:51:40.348 --> 00:51:44.394
if you had had a chance
to think things over.

581
00:51:44.644 --> 00:51:45.645
<i>I have.</i>

582
00:51:48.147 --> 00:51:51.734
But the thing is, Fiona, I just don't
really do other people's security.

583
00:51:51.818 --> 00:51:55.196
<i>Not that I don't want to.
But your infrastructure is old.</i>

584
00:51:55.530 --> 00:51:57.198
Plus the only way I could keep
you secure in the meantime

585
00:51:57.282 --> 00:52:00.827
would be by storing all your
data on my own servers.

586
00:52:00.910 --> 00:52:03.037
<i>Obviously, that would be...</i>
Yes. Jason,

587
00:52:03.121 --> 00:52:07.083
what I really want to do is announce
this tie-up at the G12 meeting.

588
00:52:07.959 --> 00:52:10.295
<i>Do we have a deal?</i>

589
00:52:19.470 --> 00:52:21.139
Good luck, sir.

590
00:52:39.824 --> 00:52:40.825
Hey.

591
00:52:40.992 --> 00:52:41.993
Sir?

592
00:52:42.076 --> 00:52:44.579
I said to get the chopper
ready. Right there.

593
00:52:44.662 --> 00:52:45.872
Sir. Right away, sir.

594
00:52:46.039 --> 00:52:47.248
Thank you.

595
00:52:47.457 --> 00:52:49.042
- Tyler, come in.
<i>- Copy.</i>

596
00:52:49.459 --> 00:52:51.419
Tyler, can you prepare
the chopper now?

597
00:52:51.544 --> 00:52:54.339
<i>We'll have everything
ready for you in a couple of minutes.</i>

598
00:53:25.661 --> 00:53:28.664
We can't keep meeting
like this, Mr. Golightly.

599
00:53:28.748 --> 00:53:30.083
Oh, yes.

600
00:53:30.166 --> 00:53:33.127
Or do you want to end this
charade and tell me your real name?

601
00:53:33.419 --> 00:53:34.962
Go.

602
00:53:37.882 --> 00:53:41.761
There's so much you don't understand
about this world you've got caught up in.

603
00:53:42.845 --> 00:53:46.224
Spare me the idiot act.
You're British Secret Service.

604
00:53:47.433 --> 00:53:51.187
Impressive work in France, by the way.
When did you realize I was a spy, too?

605
00:53:52.688 --> 00:53:55.983
Oh, pretty much straight away.

606
00:53:56.859 --> 00:53:57.902
Hmm.

607
00:54:00.279 --> 00:54:04.283
I've spent two years undercover.
Simple operation until you showed up.

608
00:54:04.492 --> 00:54:06.244
And I like
to keep things simple.

609
00:54:07.120 --> 00:54:08.996
"Simple" is my middle name.

610
00:54:13.251 --> 00:54:15.128
It would seem you've got
a choice to make.

611
00:54:17.755 --> 00:54:21.676
Temporary suspension of
hostilities? A short-term partnership?

612
00:54:22.844 --> 00:54:24.011
Agreed.
Hmm.

613
00:54:30.643 --> 00:54:31.811
Hmm.

614
00:54:31.978 --> 00:54:34.939
Politicians are even
more gullible than venture capitalists.

615
00:54:35.022 --> 00:54:36.023
<i>That is correct.</i>

616
00:54:36.107 --> 00:54:37.316
Get me a copy
of the target list.

617
00:54:37.650 --> 00:54:39.986
We'll hit them once more
just to be on the safe side.

618
00:54:40.528 --> 00:54:43.656
Give me your phone.
You don't have a phone?

619
00:54:43.781 --> 00:54:46.159
A phone will give anyone
your precise location.

620
00:54:46.242 --> 00:54:48.911
And yet they're so useful
for making phone calls.

621
00:54:48.995 --> 00:54:51.372
Excellent.
I'm not phoning anyone.

622
00:54:52.123 --> 00:54:55.042
I'm gathering evidence.

623
00:54:56.919 --> 00:55:00.756
<i>The target list, Jason.
Four iconic central London landmarks.</i>

624
00:55:00.882 --> 00:55:02.967
<i>Make your selection.
Number three.</i>

625
00:55:03.092 --> 00:55:04.927
<i>The London Eye.</i>

626
00:55:06.179 --> 00:55:11.392
<i>This cyber attack could
potentially impact 16,000 visitors.</i>

627
00:55:16.731 --> 00:55:19.233
I found him snooping
around upstairs.

628
00:55:20.318 --> 00:55:22.236
And who are you exactly?

629
00:55:22.361 --> 00:55:23.821
I'm not telling you anything.

630
00:55:23.905 --> 00:55:24.947
Hmm.

631
00:55:25.990 --> 00:55:28.159
<i>Face recognition
software launched.</i>

632
00:55:28.493 --> 00:55:31.954
<i>Johnny English is a geography
teacher from Lincolnshire.</i>

633
00:55:32.413 --> 00:55:36.250
Rather heavily armed for a lesson
on European capitals, Mr. English.

634
00:55:38.753 --> 00:55:39.962
Any thoughts, sweetheart?

635
00:55:40.963 --> 00:55:42.882
He's British Intelligence.

636
00:55:44.175 --> 00:55:46.344
And there you have it,
two words that have

637
00:55:46.427 --> 00:55:49.347
no right being
in the same sentence together.

638
00:55:49.722 --> 00:55:52.725
Do you really think
I came here alone?

639
00:55:53.100 --> 00:55:56.395
I have a team of crack
operatives out there, right now,

640
00:55:56.479 --> 00:55:57.980
just waiting to strike.

641
00:55:58.064 --> 00:55:59.357
Uh-huh.

642
00:56:04.445 --> 00:56:05.488
<i>Sir!</i>

643
00:56:08.699 --> 00:56:10.993
What has happened
to this country?

644
00:56:11.118 --> 00:56:13.829
How is it possible
that less than a century ago

645
00:56:13.913 --> 00:56:16.916
the British Empire
ruled a quarter of the globe

646
00:56:17.041 --> 00:56:20.628
and now it's relying
on someone

647
00:56:21.796 --> 00:56:24.215
like you?

648
00:56:28.761 --> 00:56:29.804
Hey! Stop!

649
00:56:31.138 --> 00:56:32.139
Stop him?

650
00:56:46.070 --> 00:56:47.071
Go.

651
00:56:55.538 --> 00:56:56.956
- Close the gates.
- Yes, sir.

652
00:57:07.842 --> 00:57:09.176
Help! Stop!

653
00:57:09.260 --> 00:57:11.637
Obstacle directly ahead,
Mrs. Trattner.

654
00:57:11.762 --> 00:57:15.683
Check your mirrors
and bring the car to a stop.

655
00:57:18.019 --> 00:57:19.729
Er, excuse me. Hey.

656
00:57:21.731 --> 00:57:22.732
Thank you.

657
00:57:26.319 --> 00:57:27.320
Drive!

658
00:57:29.614 --> 00:57:30.615
Excuse me.

659
00:57:30.698 --> 00:57:32.450
What...
What do you think you're doing?

660
00:57:32.533 --> 00:57:35.119
Excuse me!
You are not a qualified instructor.

661
00:57:44.295 --> 00:57:46.547
But what about my
instructor? Turn left.

662
00:57:46.631 --> 00:57:47.673
Oh.

663
00:57:48.549 --> 00:57:49.592
Turn right.

664
00:57:54.013 --> 00:57:56.557
For future reference,
I'm on your left.

665
00:57:56.891 --> 00:58:00.394
Please, stop.
I can't do this anymore!

666
00:58:04.774 --> 00:58:06.359
I can't see anything now!

667
00:58:06.859 --> 00:58:07.860
Good.

668
00:58:19.538 --> 00:58:21.499
When I say "go,"
turn sharp right.

669
00:58:21.582 --> 00:58:22.792
Uh-huh.

670
00:58:26.587 --> 00:58:28.839
Three, two, one.

671
00:58:29.340 --> 00:58:30.341
Go!

672
00:58:33.594 --> 00:58:35.513
And straighten up,
straighten up, straighten up.

673
00:58:35.596 --> 00:58:36.806
And go!

674
00:58:37.598 --> 00:58:38.599
Let's go, let's go.

675
00:58:47.400 --> 00:58:49.318
Oh, now just bear left
a little. Good.

676
00:58:49.735 --> 00:58:51.112
Straighten up, straighten up.

677
00:58:55.574 --> 00:58:56.575
Good!

678
00:59:00.705 --> 00:59:02.998
Well, that was
very good, Mrs. Trattner.

679
00:59:05.751 --> 00:59:07.962
I think you made
some real progress today.

680
00:59:09.547 --> 00:59:11.006
<i>You're
not hearing me, English.</i>

681
00:59:11.090 --> 00:59:14.093
<i>Given the Prime Minister's new friendship
with Volta, the situation has changed.</i>

682
00:59:14.176 --> 00:59:18.806
But the facts haven't, sir. That
attack is Volta's responsibility.

683
00:59:18.889 --> 00:59:21.350
According to you, but not
according to anyone else.

684
00:59:21.434 --> 00:59:22.852
Is he here yet?

685
00:59:23.477 --> 00:59:25.855
Good afternoon, Prime
Minister. So, this is, uh...

686
00:59:26.105 --> 00:59:28.899
English, Prime Minister.
Johnny English.

687
00:59:29.191 --> 00:59:31.694
What exactly do you
have to say for yourself?

688
00:59:31.986 --> 00:59:33.738
Rather a lot, actually.

689
00:59:34.029 --> 00:59:37.616
However, men like me don't deal
in prevarication, Prime Minister,

690
00:59:37.700 --> 00:59:39.368
so let me get
straight to the point.

691
00:59:39.452 --> 00:59:42.705
Jason Volta is the man
behind these attacks.

692
00:59:42.788 --> 00:59:45.374
And I have the evidence
to prove it.

693
00:59:46.417 --> 00:59:50.129
I managed to record this
inside Volta's country lair.

694
00:59:50.254 --> 00:59:51.756
But I should warn you,
Prime Minister,

695
00:59:51.881 --> 00:59:55.801
that what you're about to see
is evil incarnate.

696
00:59:57.803 --> 00:59:59.013
Hmm.

697
01:00:01.223 --> 01:00:04.185
<i>Here we are
at Fifi's third birthday!</i>

698
01:00:04.268 --> 01:00:06.520
<i>And it's a very exciting day!</i>

699
01:00:08.314 --> 01:00:11.066
<i>Hip hip, hooray!
Hip hip, hooray!</i>

700
01:00:12.109 --> 01:00:15.279
<i>Happy birthday to you</i>

701
01:00:16.447 --> 01:00:20.284
<i>Happy birthday to you</i>

702
01:00:21.660 --> 01:00:22.661
Thank you.

703
01:00:23.120 --> 01:00:25.539
Can I just ask,
what is wrong with you?

704
01:00:26.832 --> 01:00:29.210
The country is in a state
of complete chaos.

705
01:00:29.293 --> 01:00:30.461
The press is wetting itself,

706
01:00:30.544 --> 01:00:32.505
and the only person
capable of saving us

707
01:00:32.588 --> 01:00:34.840
is the man you're accusing
of high treason.

708
01:00:35.800 --> 01:00:39.094
I was in the room myself when
he gave the order, Prime Minister!

709
01:00:39.220 --> 01:00:40.429
But there was a...

710
01:00:40.513 --> 01:00:42.097
Do you know what I was
in the room with, English?

711
01:00:42.223 --> 01:00:43.849
Your file, which I've read,
in its entirety,

712
01:00:43.933 --> 01:00:44.975
and I have a few questions.

713
01:00:45.100 --> 01:00:46.644
Did you or did you not burn

714
01:00:46.727 --> 01:00:49.188
the Cote de Roc restaurant in
Antibes to the ground?

715
01:00:49.271 --> 01:00:50.356
Um...

716
01:00:50.439 --> 01:00:52.817
And did you or did you
not fire a guided missile

717
01:00:52.942 --> 01:00:54.568
at a peloton
of French cyclists?

718
01:00:55.110 --> 01:00:56.111
Well...

719
01:00:56.237 --> 01:00:57.655
Before commandeering
an open-top bus

720
01:00:57.780 --> 01:00:59.907
and tossing the tour guide
off the top deck,

721
01:01:00.032 --> 01:01:02.243
and then assaulting an 82-year-old
grandmother in a sandwich shop

722
01:01:02.368 --> 01:01:04.620
before battering the employee
of said sandwich shop

723
01:01:04.703 --> 01:01:06.622
with two organic
sourdough baguettes?

724
01:01:07.748 --> 01:01:09.500
Uh, I don't remember the...

725
01:01:09.625 --> 01:01:12.711
Do you have any idea
how hard it is to be me?

726
01:01:14.296 --> 01:01:15.923
- Uh...
- Hmm?

727
01:01:16.841 --> 01:01:18.843
Do you have even
the foggiest notion

728
01:01:18.968 --> 01:01:22.471
of how virtually impossible
it is to get anything done

729
01:01:22.596 --> 01:01:27.268
in the face of events
and facts and voters

730
01:01:27.393 --> 01:01:30.521
and that tsunami of tosspots
we call "the national press"?

731
01:01:30.646 --> 01:01:33.983
Finally I get the chance to do
something good for my country,

732
01:01:34.066 --> 01:01:35.317
and what happens?

733
01:01:35.442 --> 01:01:38.028
The universe sends me you.

734
01:01:39.780 --> 01:01:41.323
Well, do you know what I say?

735
01:01:41.407 --> 01:01:44.326
I say, up the universe's arse!

736
01:01:44.451 --> 01:01:46.495
And do you know what
else I say? You're fired.

737
01:01:46.579 --> 01:01:48.622
With immediate effect.
Now get out!

738
01:01:48.998 --> 01:01:53.043
And make sure I never clap
eyes on that imbecile ever again!

739
01:02:35.002 --> 01:02:36.837
What
are you doing, sir?

740
01:02:37.922 --> 01:02:41.050
What do you think I'm doing,
Bough? I'm going home.

741
01:02:41.425 --> 01:02:43.844
But the Prime Minister is
finalizing her deal with Volta.

742
01:02:43.969 --> 01:02:47.222
She's taking him to the G12 Summit
in Scotland as her special guest.

743
01:02:47.348 --> 01:02:51.352
It's over, Bough. And there's
absolutely nothing we can do about it.

744
01:02:52.061 --> 01:02:54.730
But, sir, I have a plan.

745
01:02:55.105 --> 01:02:56.899
Remember my wife?

746
01:03:05.783 --> 01:03:07.076
Clear your baffles.

747
01:03:07.785 --> 01:03:09.578
What?
Mind your head, sir.

748
01:03:09.662 --> 01:03:10.746
Ow!

749
01:03:13.832 --> 01:03:15.084
This says we're sinking.

750
01:03:18.754 --> 01:03:23.634
She's old and a little rusty, but she
can put on a hell of a fireworks display.

751
01:03:40.526 --> 01:03:42.319
Excellent work, Commander.

752
01:03:42.611 --> 01:03:45.406
Jeremy has always spoken very
highly of you, Agent English.

753
01:03:46.573 --> 01:03:47.574
Who?

754
01:03:49.493 --> 01:03:50.661
Oh.

755
01:03:50.744 --> 01:03:52.413
Oh, yes, yes.

756
01:03:54.289 --> 01:03:56.417
I'm no fan of the pen
pushers myself, so

757
01:03:56.500 --> 01:03:58.460
when orders came through
stationing us here for the Summit,

758
01:03:58.544 --> 01:04:00.963
well, I thought a lift
was the least I could do.

759
01:04:01.296 --> 01:04:03.215
Right, let's get
a move on, Bough.

760
01:04:04.633 --> 01:04:06.385
Oh, if you wouldn't mind
keeping your mobiles off

761
01:04:06.468 --> 01:04:07.803
until you're well clear,
gentlemen.

762
01:04:07.886 --> 01:04:10.389
The launch systems on the
missiles are a bit 1980s.

763
01:04:10.472 --> 01:04:13.225
Gets a tad twitchy
around microwave radiation.

764
01:04:13.350 --> 01:04:17.354
No problem there, Commander.
We're doing this mission old-school.

765
01:04:27.489 --> 01:04:29.158
This spot is perfect.

766
01:04:30.743 --> 01:04:32.077
Come on.

767
01:04:47.593 --> 01:04:48.594
Sorry, sir.

768
01:04:48.677 --> 01:04:50.137
Come on, come on...

769
01:04:52.014 --> 01:04:53.766
Right, Bough. Our
mission here is simple.

770
01:04:53.932 --> 01:04:57.311
Gain access to Volta's bedroom
and take him out.

771
01:04:57.728 --> 01:04:59.354
How are you going
to get up there, though, sir?

772
01:05:00.064 --> 01:05:03.358
A walk in the park
for the exoskeleton.

773
01:05:09.823 --> 01:05:12.868
Remotely operated
neoprene bodysuit.

774
01:05:12.993 --> 01:05:15.913
Increases the wearer's
strength 100 times.

775
01:05:16.288 --> 01:05:19.583
Right, power it up. Stick in
the floppy disk and let's go.

776
01:05:27.883 --> 01:05:28.884
Just...

777
01:05:45.359 --> 01:05:46.568
Crikey, sir!

778
01:06:03.001 --> 01:06:04.837
When will
the weapon be ready?

779
01:06:04.962 --> 01:06:08.590
<i>As soon as the Prime
Minister signs the agreement, tonight.</i>

780
01:06:08.715 --> 01:06:10.050
How do I fire it?

781
01:06:10.175 --> 01:06:12.761
<i>Press once and the attack
is launched.</i>

782
01:06:13.011 --> 01:06:16.473
<i>After which, the data
of every G12 country</i>

783
01:06:16.598 --> 01:06:20.102
<i>will be transferred to the
servers onboard the</i> Dot Calm.

784
01:06:20.185 --> 01:06:21.186
Perfect.

785
01:06:22.855 --> 01:06:23.939
Ah.

786
01:06:25.357 --> 01:06:26.358
Cheers.

787
01:06:34.783 --> 01:06:38.078
You're working for Russian Intelligence
and you have been from the start.

788
01:06:38.579 --> 01:06:41.331
Which is why I've taken an antidote
to the poison you keep in your ring,

789
01:06:41.415 --> 01:06:43.083
and which you've poured
into this drink.

790
01:06:44.835 --> 01:06:47.129
And removed the firing pin
from that pistol.

791
01:06:55.971 --> 01:06:57.931
Everyone has to make a life
for themselves.

792
01:06:58.223 --> 01:07:00.350
It's just sad that yours is

793
01:07:01.435 --> 01:07:02.477
over.

794
01:07:02.561 --> 01:07:03.645
Hmm.

795
01:07:03.729 --> 01:07:07.024
Fresh from my 3D printer.
Hundred percent plastic.

796
01:07:10.235 --> 01:07:11.904
And 100% deadly.

797
01:07:13.071 --> 01:07:14.990
Killing me won't save you.

798
01:07:15.908 --> 01:07:16.909
Don't bet on it.

799
01:07:21.663 --> 01:07:24.041
Seriously,
this cannot be happening.

800
01:07:24.249 --> 01:07:26.126
Oh, but it is.

801
01:07:27.169 --> 01:07:28.337
Drop the gun.

802
01:07:29.254 --> 01:07:30.589
Get your hands in the air.

803
01:07:31.548 --> 01:07:32.549
And you.

804
01:07:40.641 --> 01:07:41.934
There's no time
for this, Johnny.

805
01:07:42.809 --> 01:07:44.269
Oh, it isn't possible.

806
01:07:44.353 --> 01:07:47.105
You cannot be working
with this English idiot!

807
01:07:47.189 --> 01:07:50.609
Save the pillow talk
for your prison cell, Volta.

808
01:07:50.943 --> 01:07:54.780
Are you inside, sir? Yes, yes,
Bough, you can power down.

809
01:07:55.155 --> 01:07:56.990
Everything is under control.

810
01:07:57.950 --> 01:07:59.284
Shut down.

811
01:08:23.850 --> 01:08:26.270
An historic venue
for an historic meeting.

812
01:08:26.353 --> 01:08:30.274
The delegates from each G12 member
nation will have their own priorities...

813
01:08:41.618 --> 01:08:43.161
How do we get in now, sir?

814
01:08:51.920 --> 01:08:53.588
What's the plan?

815
01:09:28.665 --> 01:09:30.083
Hey, you!

816
01:09:30.751 --> 01:09:31.835
Hey!

817
01:09:47.893 --> 01:09:50.687
Thank you very much. I hope
you have everything you need.

818
01:10:07.579 --> 01:10:08.789
Ow!

819
01:10:09.039 --> 01:10:10.582
On behalf
of the United Kingdom,

820
01:10:10.707 --> 01:10:14.252
may I welcome you here today
to this ancient meeting chamber

821
01:10:14.378 --> 01:10:16.671
where the great Scottish clans

822
01:10:16.797 --> 01:10:20.550
once settled their differences
and forged new alliances.

823
01:10:21.301 --> 01:10:23.512
A place I have
specifically chosen

824
01:10:23.595 --> 01:10:26.807
in order to make
a very special announcement.

825
01:10:27.808 --> 01:10:28.809
Sir?

826
01:10:30.102 --> 01:10:34.064
Are you all right, sir?
No, I'm not all right. Get me up, Bough.

827
01:10:37.776 --> 01:10:41.321
It's very heavy, sir.
I know how heavy it is, Bough.

828
01:10:44.241 --> 01:10:45.951
We've got to get
to the conference...

829
01:10:47.869 --> 01:10:50.080
To the conference room
before Volta...

830
01:10:51.790 --> 01:10:54.000
Before Volta triggers
his weapon.

831
01:10:55.544 --> 01:10:59.339
And so, with my signature
on this agreement...

832
01:11:01.049 --> 01:11:03.135
...it gives me
great pleasure, oh,

833
01:11:03.218 --> 01:11:07.931
to welcome to you my guest,
my friend, Jason Volta.

834
01:11:10.851 --> 01:11:14.187
<i>Standing
by to launch attack, Jason.</i>

835
01:11:14.479 --> 01:11:16.648
Damn it, get me out
of this stuff. Johnny?

836
01:11:16.773 --> 01:11:18.775
- I can't see the join, sir.
- It's the clasp.

837
01:11:18.900 --> 01:11:21.862
Release the clasp and the
top and the bottom separate.

838
01:11:23.822 --> 01:11:25.782
Must have jammed
when you fell over, sir.

839
01:11:25.949 --> 01:11:27.993
For goodness sake.
Wait. Try this.

840
01:11:34.875 --> 01:11:36.877
That is quite
a lot of oil, sir.

841
01:11:37.961 --> 01:11:40.380
Oh, come on!
Come on, come on...

842
01:11:41.506 --> 01:11:45.218
Can you imagine what the world
would look like if it was run by Apple?

843
01:11:46.678 --> 01:11:49.097
Or Google? Or...

844
01:11:49.639 --> 01:11:50.724
Me?

845
01:11:53.977 --> 01:11:56.062
Do you think
you'd have failing schools?

846
01:11:56.813 --> 01:11:59.149
Do you think you'd have
endless waiting in your hospitals?

847
01:11:59.232 --> 01:12:00.233
No.

848
01:12:00.317 --> 01:12:03.069
Think you'd have such
long lines in your airports?

849
01:12:03.195 --> 01:12:04.738
- No.
- No.

850
01:12:05.071 --> 01:12:09.493
No, because all of these are
simple data management problems.

851
01:12:09.618 --> 01:12:12.287
And people like me,
we love data.

852
01:12:13.038 --> 01:12:15.707
We live for data.

853
01:12:16.124 --> 01:12:17.834
Ha!
My...

854
01:12:17.959 --> 01:12:20.295
Do you know
what I live for, Volta?

855
01:12:20.378 --> 01:12:21.379
God.

856
01:12:21.463 --> 01:12:26.843
Eliminating the threat that lying
villains like you pose to this country.

857
01:12:27.135 --> 01:12:28.345
Oh, for God's sake.

858
01:12:28.637 --> 01:12:30.180
Who is he?

859
01:12:30.347 --> 01:12:31.765
Arrest this whack job.

860
01:12:31.890 --> 01:12:34.976
The only person ordering an
arrest around here will be me.

861
01:12:35.769 --> 01:12:38.146
There's no cause for concern,
ladies and gentlemen,

862
01:12:38.271 --> 01:12:42.943
you are now in the capable hands
of Her Majesty's Secret Service.

863
01:12:43.276 --> 01:12:47.948
And you, my friend, are in for
an uncomfortable ride.

864
01:13:04.464 --> 01:13:05.799
Where was I?

865
01:13:07.259 --> 01:13:09.010
Living for data.

866
01:13:09.386 --> 01:13:10.470
Exactly.

867
01:13:11.805 --> 01:13:16.810
My algorithms can solve every one of
your problems as long as I have one thing.

868
01:13:16.893 --> 01:13:17.978
Control.

869
01:13:18.645 --> 01:13:21.982
And that is what you are about
to give me now.

870
01:13:22.607 --> 01:13:24.776
Jason, I wonder
if you could just clarify...

871
01:13:24.859 --> 01:13:25.944
Shut up.

872
01:13:26.486 --> 01:13:27.737
Now, hold on.

873
01:13:29.072 --> 01:13:30.740
<i>Castle now locked down</i>

874
01:13:31.783 --> 01:13:34.035
<i>and under your control, Jason.</i>

875
01:13:35.996 --> 01:13:38.415
The agreement this ignoramus
just signed

876
01:13:38.498 --> 01:13:41.167
didn't just give me access
to all the UK's data.

877
01:13:41.293 --> 01:13:45.255
It also gave me access to a
junction box, in North Ayrshire

878
01:13:45.380 --> 01:13:47.924
that connects
the entire World Wide Web.

879
01:13:48.216 --> 01:13:53.888
Disable the fiber-optic cables in that
box and the Internet will cease to exist.

880
01:13:55.181 --> 01:13:57.767
Johnny? Are you okay?

881
01:14:05.108 --> 01:14:07.944
Have you got a phone?
We need to call for backup.

882
01:14:08.028 --> 01:14:10.989
There's no time for backup.
I'm going after Volta.

883
01:14:11.072 --> 01:14:12.782
And don't lose that one!

884
01:14:13.825 --> 01:14:17.746
Do you understand what it
means if I turn the Internet off?

885
01:14:17.954 --> 01:14:22.292
Cities will go dark. Planes
will fall out of the sky.

886
01:14:23.001 --> 01:14:26.463
Trains will collide.
Law and order will break down

887
01:14:26.546 --> 01:14:29.424
and the world as you know it
will be over.

888
01:14:30.133 --> 01:14:32.761
Show, don't tell, right?

889
01:14:36.556 --> 01:14:38.558
<i>Initiating attack, Jason.</i>

890
01:14:39.476 --> 01:14:41.478
<i>Taking control
of junction box.</i>

891
01:14:42.604 --> 01:14:47.484
<i>Suspending Internet and electricity
supply across Britain and Europe.</i>

892
01:14:48.526 --> 01:14:50.945
<i>Stage one of attack complete.</i>

893
01:14:51.446 --> 01:14:54.741
Ladies and gentlemen.
I can stop the attack

894
01:14:54.824 --> 01:14:58.328
as long as each of you signs the
same agreement as the Prime Minister,

895
01:14:58.411 --> 01:15:00.413
giving me complete control.

896
01:15:01.331 --> 01:15:02.749
Your call.

897
01:15:03.583 --> 01:15:06.378
<i>Welcome to British Intelligence.</i>
Get me Pegasus!

898
01:15:06.795 --> 01:15:10.548
<i>For MI5, press one.
For MI6, press two.</i>

899
01:15:10.965 --> 01:15:13.301
<i>For MI7, press three.</i>

900
01:15:19.891 --> 01:15:23.061
<i>Eight G12 signatures
now acquired.</i>

901
01:15:24.104 --> 01:15:26.690
Signal the chopper,
we're almost done here.

902
01:15:27.107 --> 01:15:28.900
<i>For accounts, press five.</i>

903
01:15:28.983 --> 01:15:31.319
<i>For childcare services, press six.</i>
Oh, come on!

904
01:15:31.444 --> 01:15:33.780
<i>For more options, press seven.</i>

905
01:15:36.324 --> 01:15:37.325
What?

906
01:15:38.743 --> 01:15:43.915
<i>Only two further signatures required
to achieve control of G12 nations' data.</i>

907
01:15:44.749 --> 01:15:46.167
<i>All UK data</i>

908
01:15:46.251 --> 01:15:49.045
<i>now successfully transferred
to the</i> Dot Calm.

909
01:15:49.170 --> 01:15:52.674
<i>For Aphrodite,
press one. For Pegasus, press two.</i>

910
01:15:55.218 --> 01:15:56.219
Oh, my God.

911
01:15:56.302 --> 01:16:00.014
<i>Dive the submarine.
Repeat, dive the submarine.</i>

912
01:16:02.809 --> 01:16:04.936
Director's office?
<i>This is Johnny English.</i>

913
01:16:05.061 --> 01:16:09.274
I need to speak to Pegasus
immediately. It's a national emergency.

914
01:16:09.399 --> 01:16:10.900
One moment, please, sir.

915
01:16:12.861 --> 01:16:13.903
<i>This is</i> HMS Vengeance.

916
01:16:14.028 --> 01:16:17.657
We have a full launch code.
Repeat, launch code is locked.

917
01:16:17.782 --> 01:16:19.784
<i>Do I have your permission
to fire?</i>

918
01:16:19.909 --> 01:16:22.245
Oh, my God. Could you hold on
one moment, please?

919
01:16:22.370 --> 01:16:24.122
Sir? Sir!

920
01:16:25.081 --> 01:16:26.082
Hello?

921
01:16:26.332 --> 01:16:27.333
<i>Hello?</i>

922
01:16:27.417 --> 01:16:30.545
Sir! <i>HMS Vengeance</i> here. Do I
have your permission to launch?

923
01:16:30.670 --> 01:16:33.590
<i>What? Listen,
we have to call in an attack.</i>

924
01:16:33.673 --> 01:16:34.924
<i>Did you say
"attack," sir?</i>

925
01:16:35.008 --> 01:16:37.343
<i>Yes, an attack. Attack.</i>

926
01:16:38.720 --> 01:16:41.389
General quarters,
we are go for launch.

927
01:16:41.514 --> 01:16:43.433
Target coordinates locked,
Commander.

928
01:16:43.558 --> 01:16:44.559
Hello?

929
01:16:46.478 --> 01:16:47.520
Hello?

930
01:16:57.947 --> 01:17:00.492
Commander, the
missile is being redirected.

931
01:17:01.326 --> 01:17:03.995
It seems to be locking on
to a new hostile target.

932
01:17:06.623 --> 01:17:07.999
What's a "Sherbet F"?

933
01:17:19.302 --> 01:17:21.429
Oh, no. What was
that?

934
01:17:22.972 --> 01:17:26.017
Dot Calm <i>appears
to be offline, Jason.</i>

935
01:17:26.184 --> 01:17:28.853
<i>The cyber attack
has been halted.</i>

936
01:17:32.899 --> 01:17:34.234
Did you

937
01:17:34.609 --> 01:17:37.195
make a call quite close
to the submarine, sir?

938
01:17:40.073 --> 01:17:41.199
Um...

939
01:17:41.282 --> 01:17:42.367
Because...

940
01:17:43.368 --> 01:17:44.702
You did it, sir!

941
01:17:45.870 --> 01:17:47.622
Mission accomplished!

942
01:17:48.164 --> 01:17:49.666
Well, exactly!

943
01:17:51.417 --> 01:17:54.504
<i>I am re-evaluating
our options, Jason.</i>

944
01:18:01.010 --> 01:18:02.846
Johnny! Johnny!

945
01:18:02.929 --> 01:18:06.015
Volta is getting away! He's
heading for his helicopter!

946
01:18:06.099 --> 01:18:07.392
No, Bough.

947
01:18:08.601 --> 01:18:10.270
This one's mine.

948
01:18:43.887 --> 01:18:45.555
Careful, sir. Sir?

949
01:18:56.608 --> 01:18:58.276
Last two steps, sir.

950
01:19:03.364 --> 01:19:05.283
Not so fast, Volta!

951
01:19:06.910 --> 01:19:08.995
Is this supposed to scare me,
Sir Lancelot?

952
01:19:14.125 --> 01:19:15.376
Take cover, Bough.

953
01:19:22.008 --> 01:19:25.553
Don't worry, he's only got six
bullets in that thing.

954
01:19:29.015 --> 01:19:30.725
And, of course,
the thing itself.

955
01:19:33.144 --> 01:19:35.188
You've run out
of options, Volta.

956
01:19:36.022 --> 01:19:37.315
Oh, you think you've won?

957
01:19:37.398 --> 01:19:38.608
Mmm.

958
01:19:39.192 --> 01:19:42.236
<i>Rerouting the attack
to our Nevada servers, Jason.</i>

959
01:19:42.862 --> 01:19:46.866
The world's going down, English.
And I'll be the last man standing.

960
01:19:47.492 --> 01:19:50.536
Goodbye, English!
Goodbye, Internet.

961
01:19:51.788 --> 01:19:56.459
I've got it. That's a Gazelle
341 light attack helicopter.

962
01:19:57.043 --> 01:19:59.545
If we can hack into
its operating system,

963
01:19:59.796 --> 01:20:01.798
we can disable
the drive function.

964
01:20:02.090 --> 01:20:03.091
Here.

965
01:20:06.928 --> 01:20:11.057
Look at you! You couldn't use
that thing if your life depended on it!

966
01:20:14.018 --> 01:20:15.395
Let's get outta here.

967
01:20:16.104 --> 01:20:17.814
Get this steel bird in the...

968
01:20:23.027 --> 01:20:27.949
<i>Rerouting complete. Attack
data now installed at our Nevada servers.</i>

969
01:20:28.366 --> 01:20:30.159
<i>Should I initiate?</i>

970
01:20:30.576 --> 01:20:31.577
<i>Jason?</i>

971
01:20:36.249 --> 01:20:38.418
<i>Should I initiate
the new attack?</i>

972
01:20:39.460 --> 01:20:41.963
Initiate this!

973
01:20:42.046 --> 01:20:44.465
Jason.

974
01:20:55.727 --> 01:20:57.061
Well, uh,
ladies and gentlemen.

975
01:20:57.186 --> 01:21:01.065
I think we can all agree, that wasn't
quite the evening we were expecting.

976
01:21:06.404 --> 01:21:08.406
I had hoped to
present to you tonight...

977
01:21:08.531 --> 01:21:10.825
Thank you... a vision
of what Britain might be.

978
01:21:11.242 --> 01:21:14.996
But, as it happens, the man
who saved us all this evening,

979
01:21:15.079 --> 01:21:18.624
the man who, I might add, I
personally assigned to this case,

980
01:21:19.250 --> 01:21:21.461
has presented us with
a different kind of vision.

981
01:21:21.544 --> 01:21:25.840
A living embodiment, if you like, of
those fundamental British qualities

982
01:21:25.923 --> 01:21:30.219
that have ensured that our
beloved island nation endures.

983
01:21:30.720 --> 01:21:33.639
Courage under fire,
endless ingenuity

984
01:21:33.723 --> 01:21:35.641
and above all, a quiet

985
01:21:36.267 --> 01:21:38.978
unassailable dignity.

986
01:21:58.122 --> 01:21:59.373
Thank you.

987
01:22:06.547 --> 01:22:07.965
All together.

988
01:22:18.851 --> 01:22:20.561
Welcome back, Mr. English.

989
01:22:20.645 --> 01:22:21.813
Thank you, Headmaster.

990
01:22:21.896 --> 01:22:23.606
Thank you for agreeing
to be our guest speaker.

991
01:22:23.689 --> 01:22:26.484
Now the governors and staff are
all waiting for us in the rose garden.

992
01:22:26.567 --> 01:22:29.487
Yes, if you could just excuse
me for a few minutes, Headmaster.

993
01:22:35.243 --> 01:22:36.244
Oh.

994
01:22:38.121 --> 01:22:39.372
Morning, sir!
Hello, sir!

995
01:22:39.455 --> 01:22:41.707
Welcome back, sir!

996
01:22:45.753 --> 01:22:46.838
Surprise!

997
01:22:47.797 --> 01:22:48.965
Thank you.

998
01:22:50.174 --> 01:22:51.759
Where's Straker?

999
01:22:52.677 --> 01:22:54.470
Good.
Here, sir.

